cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for transferring temporal knowledge, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of information asymmetry, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
